It's possible to add archived version to issue via REST but it's not possible to remove it with REST (operation succeeds but the archived version gets added again on saving).
According to [this comment|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-6419?focusedCommentId=34398&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-34398] adding/removing archived versions to/from an issue should not be possible.

Reproduction steps (tested on 6.3.13)
1. Create an Issue and a Version (mark it as archived).
2. Create following data.txt file:
{noformat}
{
   "update" : {
       "versions" : [{"add" : {"name" : "NAME_OF_YOUR_VERSION"}}]
   }
}
{noformat}
3. Execute curl:
{noformat}
curl -D- -u USER:PASS -X PUT --data @data.txt -H "Content-Type: application/json" http://HOST:PORT/jira/rest/api/2/issue/ISSUE_KEY
{noformat}
4. Check the issue in browser, it should now have this archive version added in "Affects Version/s" field.

Once this archived version has been added it cannot be removed via REST (neither it can be removed in UI for that matter) i.e. changing "add" to "remove" in above {{data.txt}} file and executing the PUT again with curl does not remove the version.

A workaround is to unmark this version as archived and then update the issue.

