At the moment, adding/removing any issues from Sprints is considered an update and JIRA will send an Issue Updated notification. However, some times users add/remove issues from Sprints multiple times before confirming. This will cause many emails to be sent. Removing users from the Issue Updated notification is not an option because the users will still need to know when other important details are updated.

It would be good to have an option so that issues added/removed from Sprints will *not* send email notifications.

When the validation is ok but the actual update operation fails the error will be discarded. This is unlikely to happen but still is a possibility.
This is due to the lines below:
{code}
            IssueService.IssueResult result = issueService.update(getLoggedInUser(), updateValidationResult);
            result = issueService.getIssue(getLoggedInUser(), getIssueId());
{code}

When the issueService.update() returns an error it's simply discarded. This may happen when {{IssueManager}} will throw an exception (for example validation of custom text fields length - not yet implemented but will be there).

The 2nd line (issueService.getIssue()) has been added as a fix against disappearing archived fix version on inline issue edit.
